content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Review and Publish Replies

After Einstein has identified common responses in your transcripts, select and review the most useful replies, and then publish them to your agents.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Einstein Reply Recommendations is included in the Einstein for Service add-on license.
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To publish and manage replies:	
Create on quick text AND Manage Replies for Einstein Reply Recommendations AND View Setup and Configuration

After your model is built, the Einstein Reply Recommendations Setup page lists up to 100 common replies that Einstein has identified from your closed chats. Review, curate, and publish these reply candidates to QuickText so they can be recommended to agents.

Review and fine-tune the candidate replies to fit your company voice and agent needs. Replace specific product names and customer information with merge fields, so that replies are applicable across chats.
To publish replies, select them and click Publish Candidates to Quick Text.

Add information about the replies that you’re publishing, such as which Quick Text folder to save your replies in and the channels where they’re available.
Record Type	If prompted, select a quick text record type to customize access to the replies.
Quick Text Name	Optionally, change the reply’s name from an auto-generated number to something more meaningful.
Folder	Select a quick text folder to store the replies in. Agents need access to the folder that you select to view the replies as recommendations or quick text.
Category	Select a quick text category. Categories are customizable and make it easier to search for quick text.
Channel	Optionally, select which channels agents can access and search for the replies as quick text.

Click Publish. The replies’ status in the list changes from New to Published to Quick Text.

Give Agents Access to Reply Recommendations

After you publish your replies, give agents access to reply recommendations and activate your model.
title: Reviewing and Publishing Einstein Reply Recommendations
